  "text": "In this paper, we conducted a large genome-wide CNV analysis of 2500 BRCA1 pathogenic variant carriers, with or without breast and/or ovarian cancer, using a previously published SNP-based genome-wide association study. [CITATION_1] To maximize the sensitivity for CNV discovery, multiple CNV calling algorithms were applied to the data set. Analyses identified several putative CNVs overlapping gene regions associated with risk of breast or ovarian cancer for BRCA1 pathogenic variant carriers and a requirement for validation in larger studies.",
